                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Rectangular off-white marble plaque broken down the middle and reconnected. Seemingly intact, but chipped along the left and top edges. The rear is smooth.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">21.6</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">29.5</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">1.7-2.0</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.complete.broken"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Five lines of Greek text, centred on the stone, with a consistent left margin, and final line (numerals) centred between ivy leaves.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.complete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Letters are deeply v-cut, somewhat elongated, and showing some tendency towards curvature in e.g. the M. Minial use of serifs. Lunate omega, but rectilinear epsilon and sigma. Alpha with broken bar; mu with four full-length, slanting strokes; kappa with short ams; omicron ovoid but full height; epsilon tall and thin, all bars of equal length; zeta an equal length Z. Use of interpunct to mark off the names, and hedera around the numeral.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line1">Line 1</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">29-38</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line2" to="line2">Line 2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">25-30</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line3" to="line5">Line 3-5</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">30-34</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <height unit="mm"/>
                                </dimensions>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
